SIMPLE: warning
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warning
<hw>Warn"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Giving previous notice;
cautioning; admonishing; <as>as, a <ex>warning</ex>
voice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>warning</qex> timepiece never ceased.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Warning piece</b></col>, <col><b>Warning
wheel</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Horol.)</fld>, <cd>a piece or wheel which
produces a sound shortly before the clock strikes.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warning</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Warning
<hw>Warn"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Previous notice.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧At a month's <xex>warning</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A great journey to take upon so short a <qex>warning</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Caution against danger, or against faults or evil
practices which incur danger; admonition; monition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Could <qex>warning</qex> make the world more just or wise.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warningly</ent>⟦br⟧
